<title>USA: Conseco, Pioneer Financial shares up on deal.</title>
<headline>Conseco, Pioneer Financial shares up on deal.</headline>
<dateline>CHICAGO 1996-12-16</dateline>
<text>
<p>Shares of Conseco Inc and Pioneer Financial Services Inc were up Monday after the two companies agreed to a merger, under which Conseco would acquire Pioneer in a $477 million deal.</p>
<p>Conseco shares were up two at 61-1/2. Pioneer's stock gained 5-7/8 AT 24-3/4.</p>
<p>Conseco agreed to pay between $25 and $28 a share in its stock for Pioneer. Conseco also said it expects Pioneer to add about $0.15 per fully diluted share to its operating earnings in the first year.</p>
<p>&quot;It's a very good fit,&quot; EVEREN analyst Frederick Sandburg said.</p>
<p>((Reuters Chicago Newsdesk (312) 408-8787))</p>
